name: Snap
description:
Snap is a surfing maneuver in which the surfer comes off the bottom turn at 30-50 degrees facing the water line with his or her chest, quickly attacks the lip in the steep section and keeps riding the wave face. The snap is a challenging movement that is only done in the steeper sections of the wave.

Local surfer is making snap during surfing competition in Sri Lanka, Hikkaduwa. 2011
